# Check for near zero variance (would give correlation where there is none)
nzv_nmr <- caret::nearZeroVar(ps_nmr %>% 
                     otu_table() %>% 
                     t(),freqCut = 8/1, #(number of variables-1)/1
                     uniqueCut = 10, saveMetrics = TRUE)

# Removes non-zero predictors
ps_nzv_nmr <- prune_taxa(nzv_nmr[nzv_nmr[,"nzv"] == 0, ] %>%
                               rownames() %>%
                               as.character(),
                               ps_nmr)

# Create pairs for stat tests between alpha div
path_nmr <- levels(factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_nmr)$origin)) # get the variables
path_pairs_nmr <- combn(seq_along(path_nmr), 2, simplify = FALSE, FUN = function(i)path_nmr[i]) #creates all possible pairs

# Compute alpha diversity
alpha_nmr <- microbiome::alpha(ps_nzv_nmr, index = c('shannon', 'observed')) # Shannon (and package) most accurate

Beta diversity

PCoA

# Create dissimilarity indices
bray_nmr <- vegdist(t(otu_table(ps_nmr)), method = "bray", na.rm = T)
beta_nmr <- bray_nmr

# Principal Coordinate Analysis (PCoA)
beta_nmr <- as.data.frame(cmdscale(bray_nmr, k = 2))

# Add metadata
beta_nmr <- base::transform(merge(sample_data(ps_nmr), beta_nmr, by = 0, all = TRUE), row.names = Row.names, Row.names = NULL)

Mice

Alpha diversity

# Check for near zero variance (would give correlation where there is none)
nzv_mice <- caret::nearZeroVar(ps_mice %>% 
                     otu_table() %>% 
                     t(),freqCut = 17/1, #(number of variables-1)/1
                     uniqueCut = 10, saveMetrics = TRUE)

# Removes non-zero predictors
ps_nzv_mice <- phyloseq::prune_taxa(nzv_mice[nzv_mice[,"nzv"] == 0, ] %>%
                               rownames() %>%
                               as.character(),
                               ps_mice)

# Create pairs for stat tests between alpha div
path_mice <- levels(factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_mice)$origin)) # get the variables
path_pairs_mice <- combn(seq_along(path_mice), 2, simplify = FALSE, FUN = function(i)path_mice[i]) #creates all possible pairs

# Compute alpha diversity
alpha_mice <- microbiome::alpha(ps_nzv_mice, index = c('shannon', 'observed')) # Shannon (and package) most accurate
head(alpha_mice)
##    observed diversity_shannon
## M2       93          3.309925
## M3       64          2.913366
## M4      100          3.637588
## M5      126          3.945257
## M7       46          2.889857
## M8       55          2.944171
# Add origin column
alpha_mice$origin <- sample_data(ps_nzv_mice)$origin

# Add SI/LI/stool
alpha_mice <- alpha_mice %>% 
  mutate(region = case_when(origin == "si1"  ~ "SI",
                             origin == "si2" ~ "SI", 
                             origin == "si3" ~ "SI",
                             origin == "caecum" ~ "LI", 
                             origin == "colon" ~ "LI",
                             origin == "stool" ~ "stool")) 

section_alpha <- alpha_mice %>% 
  group_by(origin) %>% 
  summarise_at(vars(c(diversity_shannon, observed)), list(name = mean)) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, digits = 1)

Compare

Join data

# Extract OTU tables
otu_nmr <- as.data.frame(otu_table(ps_nmr))
otu_mice <- as.data.frame(otu_table(ps_mice))


# Create OTU column
otu_nmr$otu <- rownames(otu_nmr)
otu_mice$otu <- rownames(otu_mice)

# Adjust
otu_joined <- full_join(otu_nmr, otu_mice, by = "otu") %>% #join
  'rownames<-'(.$otu) %>% #set OTUs as rownames
  select(-otu) %>% #delete OTU column
  mutate_all(., ~replace_na(.,0)) %>%  #replace NA
  otu_table(., taxa_are_rows = TRUE)
# Extract sample data
sample_nmr <- data.frame(sample_data(ps_nmr)) %>% #extract sample data
  mutate(tissue = NULL, #remove tissue column
         model = rep("nmr")) %>% #create model column
  'rownames<-'(NULL) #remove rownames

Alpha diversity

# Check for near zero variance (would give correlation where there is none)
nzv_joined <- caret::nearZeroVar(ps_joined %>% 
                     otu_table() %>% 
                     t(),freqCut = 38/1, #(number of variables-1)/1
                     uniqueCut = 10, saveMetrics = TRUE)

# Removes non-zero predictors
ps_nzv_joined <- phyloseq::prune_taxa(nzv_joined[nzv_joined[,"nzv"] == 0, ] %>%
                               rownames() %>%
                               as.character(),
                               ps_joined)

# Create pairs for stat tests between alpha div
path_joined <- levels(factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_joined)$model)) # get the variables
path_pairs_joined <- combn(seq_along(path_joined), 2, simplify = FALSE, FUN = function(i)path_joined[i]) #creates all possible pairs

# Compute alpha diversity
alpha_joined <- microbiome::alpha(ps_nzv_joined, index = 'shannon') # Shannon (and package) most accurate
head(alpha_joined)
